Rating: 4
I'm not sure whether this is the same Bon Appetit recipe I've used in the past (due to spouse that is a chronic recycler of cherished magazines!. If it is there are a few errors in the recipe that make all the difference. First, should be 4 cups apples (about 3 large) instead of 4 large. Also 1 cup of chopped walnuts (I roast my) should be added to the apple mixture. Then add one cup of sour cream to the oil/egg mixture. One very critical detail (that I learned the hard way) is to make absolutely sure that the apple mixture is not in contact with the bundt pan. Remember sugar burns and may cause the cake to brown too quickly so you pull it out too soon = undercooked middle. Try filling the pan half way and pressing apples into the batter. Finally, my recipe calls for whipping cream and a caramel sauce on the side.

